description: What error the LLM sees when Monty's maxAllocations limit is exceeded
date: 2026-03-29
---
When the Monty sandbox exceeds its maxAllocations limit, Monty throws a
MontyRuntimeError with a MemoryError. The error message format is:

    MemoryError: allocation limit exceeded: <attempted> > <limit>

e.g. "MemoryError: allocation limit exceeded: 4 > 3"

The full traceback (via error.display("traceback")) looks like:

    Traceback (most recent call last):
      File "main.py", line N, in <module>
        <offending line>
        <underline>
    MemoryError: allocation limit exceeded: <attempted> > <limit>

In runSandboxCode (monty-sandbox.ts), this is caught as MontyRuntimeError
and returned as a SandboxResult with errorType "RuntimeError" and
isTimeout false (the message does not contain "time limit").

In buildFeedbackMessage (chat-orchestrator.ts), this becomes a JSON
payload sent back to the LLM as a user-role message:

    Code execution result: {"success":false,"error_type":"RuntimeError",
      "message":"Traceback (most recent call last):\n  ...\n
      MemoryError: allocation limit exceeded: 4 > 3",
      "is_timeout":false,"rounds_remaining":N}

Unlike time-limit errors, there is no special timeout_note hint. The LLM
only sees the raw MemoryError inside the traceback.

Note: the exact error wording was determined empirically by running Monty
at the version installed in this repo (not from reading Monty source).
It could change in a future @pydantic/monty release.
